coffee lounge
Homonym Number:
Word Class:noun
Sense Number:
Definition:
Origin:[none]
Register:
Register 2:
Domain:[none]
Region:[none]
See:
Pronunciation:
Notes: Jim writes: Coffee lounges as well as coffee bars and coffee houses were common in NZ in and after the mid-1950s. They still exist under this names especially in more out of the way places. I recently saw one in Dunedin and in Wanganui. Not recorded in OED or other dictionaries, nor have I noticed it in extra-NZ reading. It may be distinctive NZE.
